snippet.title: China Shoots Itself in the Foot by Declaring Air Zone; US and Japan Defiant

localized.description: China faces a daunting task of enforcing the unilateral declaration of its "Air Defense Identification Zone" (ADIZ) in the East China Sea that covers Japanese -administered Senkaku islands (Diaoyu in Chinese) and risking retaliatory action from Japan and US. Two days after China's declaration, US sent two B-52 bombers over the area as a show of support for its ally. Japan and Korea defied Beijing's newly declared by sending military over flights in the area. Taiwan, Australia and the Philippines also rejected China's claim of control of the air space as a gesture of solidarity with Japan and US. Some analyst believe that China might have shot itself in the foot by its provocative action aimed at antagonizing Japan and gradually gaining control of the disputed area.
